</taxonomicName>
by the overall yellow colour of the body with almost no markings, eXcept for the particular pattern of stripes on the dorsal part of thoraX; the wings with a slight pale yellowish tint and a total absence of coloured spots, and finally by the unique shape of the genitalia, particularly the gonostylus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
